      "updated_at": "2025-10-24T08:58:39Z",
      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Typically a warmed-up node will have up to three \"high bandwidth\" peers who are allowed to hand block data, even if one of them is being slow. During this reorg, it appears likely that all the high bandwidth peers were on the \"losing side\" of this reorg along with your node, and were unable to help unstuck the node. There is a fallback 10 minute timeout that would have eventually helped if the slow peer doesn't give you the block in time (you may see \"Timeout downloading block\" log)",
